TY  - JOUR
T1  - Effects of Age at Entry, Knowledge Intensity, and Imitability on International Growth
AU  - Autio, Erkko
AU  - Sapienza, Harry J.
AU  - Almeida, James G.
Y1  - 2000/10/01
PY  - 2000
DA  - 2000/10/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/1556419
DO  - 10.5465/1556419
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 909
EP  - 924
VL  - 43
IS  - 5
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - We employed knowledge-based theory to shed light on international growth in entrepreneurial firms. We found earlier initiation of internationalization and greater knowledge intensity to be associated with faster international growth. However, contrary to expectations, firms with more imitable technologies also grew faster. The former results suggest that early pursuit of international opportunity induces greater entrepreneurial behavior and confers a growth advantage, whereas the latter call into question current views of the role of imitability in international growth.
AB  - We employed knowledge-based theory to shed light on international growth in entrepreneurial firms. We found earlier initiation of internationalization and greater knowledge intensity to be associated with faster international growth. However, contrary to expectations, firms with more imitable technologies also grew faster. The former results suggest that early pursuit of international opportunity induces greater entrepreneurial behavior and confers a growth advantage, whereas the latter call into question current views of the role of imitability in international growth.
SN  - 0001-4273
M3  - doi: 10.5465/1556419
UR  - https://doi.org/10.5465/1556419
Y2  - 2026/04/24
